content: Great app, though it has a few spelling mistakes. In US National Parks, Capital Reef needs to be Capitol Reef and Sequoya needs to be Sequoia. replyContent: Hi! There are two versions of the app, one with ads and one without. So, to get the version without ads, you need to go to the Google Play Store and get the full version there. There is no in-app purchase.

content: The ad-related issue has been fixed with latest update. 5 stars again. Thank you :)
replyContent: We apologize for this bug. We have just released a new version (2.1.1) which corrects the problem. It will probably appear on Google Play within a few hours from now.

replyContent: If you paid and downloaded the full Android app, you now have two Seterra icons on your phone / tablet. You have to pick the right one, or you will still be seeing ads.
